      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Four months after Carl E. Vogel quit as the president and chief executive of Charter Communications, the cable company that lost $4.3 billion last year, he resurfaced last week.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Four months after Carl E. Vogel quit as the president and chief executive of Charter Communications, the cable company that lost $4.3 billion last year, he resurfaced last week.</p>
        <p>He joined the board of EchoStar Communications, which offers the Dish Network service that was a big reason for Charter's loss of 800,000 subscribers during Mr. Vogel's time there.</p>
        <p>Mark A. Stein</p>
        <p>OPENERS: SUITS</p>
